# S10-T07: GameOver Spacing Pass

## Objective
Audit and fix margin/padding on GameOverScreen so the panel fits portrait and landscape
without excess whitespace or clipped Play Again button.

## Acceptance Criteria
- Portrait: panel centred, comfortable but not wasteful (`p-6` outer, `p-6 landscape:p-4` inner).
- Landscape 667×375: panel `max-h-[90dvh]`, score `text-4xl landscape:text-4xl` (not 6xl), gap `gap-4 landscape:gap-3`.
- Mascot `w-24 h-24 landscape:w-20 landscape:h-20`.
- Play Again button always fully visible; min-height 44px touch target.
- Safe-area insets applied (`.safe-top` / horizontal landscape padding from T01).
- Optional: landscape row variant (mascot left, score copy right) if column still overflows — document choice in commit.

## Steps
1. Screenshot current GameOver at 375×667 and 667×375; note overflow/gaps.
2. Update `GameOverScreen.tsx` padding, font clamps, gap utilities.
3. Apply safe-area classes from T01 to outer wrapper.
4. Force GameOver via dev helper (T03) and verify both orientations.
5. `git commit -m "fix(layout): game over screen spacing and landscape fit"`.
